description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Part Time 30 hours per week &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An excellent opportunity has arisen to join our Stroke Service in Swansea Bay University Health Board. This exciting post, working within an in-patient setting is based on the Stroke Unit at Morriston Hospital and will have opportunities to develop skills across the whole of the Health Board’s Stroke Service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will work as part of a dynamic Multidisciplinary Team to provide rehabilitation to individuals following a stroke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post will provide the opportunity to deliver stroke specific generic rehabilitation across the patient journey facilitating seamless and timely transition from hospital to home to focus on a meaningful life after stroke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to adopt a flexible approach to work and may be expected to participate in a 7 day working rota.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder needs to be able to demonstrate significant experience in working in rehabilitation within the NHS, Social Care or community based settings. Previous therapy assistant experience and experience of working with stroke patients is highly desirable for this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An NVQ 3 and/or evidence that you are working towards the physiotherapy/occupational therapy support worker diploma or other relevant healthcare/exercise diploma is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to manage travel time effectively to optimise caseload management across sites is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will entail some administrative responsibilities, it is therefore highly desirable that the candidate has good basic IT skills and knowledge of healthcare IT systems and applications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be supported by senior therapists and the clinical team lead.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Angharad GavinLead Stroke Physiotherapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Angarad.gavin@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01792 703124&lt;/p&gt;
